params.description: Output only. Capacity of the source file share when the backup was created.

params.description: Output only. The size of the storage used by the backup. As backups share storage, this number is expected to change with backup creation/deletion.

params.description: The resource name of the source Cloud Filestore instance, in the format projects/{project_number}/locations/{location_id}/instances/{instance_id}, used to create this backup.

params.name: data.source_file_share
params.description: Name of the file share in the source Cloud Filestore instance that the backup is created from.

params.name: data.source_instance_tier
params.description: Output only. The service tier of the source Cloud Filestore instance that this backup is created from.

params.name: data.download_bytes
params.description: Output only. Amount of bytes that will be downloaded if the backup is restored. This may be different than storage bytes, since sequential backups of the same disk will share storage.

params.description: Output only. Reserved for future use.
